.TH neonstore 1 "September 2025" "NeonStore" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
neonstore \- deterministic, local-first store dataset engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B neonstore
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
NeonStore manages products and orders stored in CSV with atomic writes,
integrity sidecars, policies, backups, snapshots and auditing.
See the project README for detailed usage and examples.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B analytics summary
Emit dataset KPIs and top products (JSON by default).
.TP
.B products set-price \-\-id ID \-\-price NUM
Update product price atomically.
.TP
.B products set-stock \-\-id ID \-\-stock NUM
Update product stock atomically.
.TP
.B csv validate
Validate CSV structure and numeric fields (exit 2 on violations).
.TP
Other commands are documented in the online README and docs/.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Commands return 0 on success and non-zero on failure. See docs/EXITCODES.md.
